         <div type="translation">
            <ab>" . . .  It is good for new fistulous ulcers, for ulcers needing to be completely cicatrized, and for those that are hard to cicatrize; it is also good for chilblains and . . .  .;(Hd 2) The plaster with zinc oxide: 2 ounces of zinc oxide, 3 oz. of litharge, 2 oz. of poultry-fat, 4 oz. of wax, juice of linseed, 5 oz. of chamomile. Add the melted solubles to the triturated litharge and zinc oxide."</ab>
